You have to pay attention to variable types! a = 4 b = 3 c = (int)(a/b) TYPECASTING is a way to change one variable type into another You can use typecasting to change integers into float numbers. For instance, (float)a will change 4 into 4.0
float(c) would change c into 1.3 because it's 4/3 float(c) would change c into 1.0, because the division isn't recalculated
d = 5 e = 2 f = (float)d/(float)e; }
